James is applying for a faculty position at Stanford in Global Governance for Sustainability. His research statement highlights his interdisciplinary work as an environmental economist and computational modeler, focusing on climate change impacts and the water-energy-food nexus. Arachne provides suggestions to improve the clarity and emphasize the relevance of his research. The recommendations include refining the introductory paragraph, reorganizing the content under specific thematic headings, strengthening the connection to global governance, and highlighting teaching experience aligned with sustainability. Arachne also provides a revised version of the first few paragraphs incorporating these suggestions.
